@Node "POWERDOTS" "NetCall_English.guide/POWERDOTS"
@Next "CRIGHT"
@Toc "ALL"

Features of NetCall
===================

   @{b}*@{ub} Simplifies the treatment of file-requests and crash-mails (pending
     jobs are displayed in a list-view-gadget).

   @{b}*@{ub} Enables automatic polling on all lines of the destination system
     (if one line is @{i}BUSY@{ui}, @{b}NetCall@{ub} will automatically dial up the next
     line).

   @{b}*@{ub} Includes #?.REQ-file editor ('request file') to create or edit
     .REQ-files  in the @{i}OUTBOUND@{ui}-directory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Searches (even when your mailer polls already) for other lines  of
     the destination system in the nodelist (crashing or frequesting).

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports/simplifies multi-bossing.

   @{b}*@{ub} Simplifies polling on a line of your boss, which is not listed in
     the  nodelist.

   @{b}*@{ub} Hides your own password when crashing or frequesting.

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports TrapDoor in resident or in shell-mode.

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports automatical operation (without user-interaction).

   @{b}*@{ub} User-defineable toolbox.

   @{b}*@{ub} ARexx-interface.

   @{b}*@{ub} Font-sensitive GUI.

   @{b}*@{ub} Opens public-screen if desired.

   @{b}*@{ub} User-defineable menus (user-commands).

   @{b}*@{ub} Extensive ways to configure.

   @{b}*@{ub} Many shell-arguments.

   @{b}*@{ub} Localized (OS2.1 and better).

   @{b}*@{ub} Iconify-function (including @{i}QUIET@{ui}-mode).


@EndNode

