@Node "HARDWARE" "NetCall_English.guide/HARDWARE"
@Next "SOFTWARE"
@Toc "INSTALL"

Assumptions to the hardware
===========================

   @{b}NetCall@{ub} does not make any assumptions to the hardware.   @{b}NetCall@{ub}
runs on every Amiga with at least 512 KB RAM.


@EndNode

@Node "SOFTWARE" "NetCall_English.guide/SOFTWARE"
@Next "INSTALLER"
@Prev "HARDWARE"
@Toc "INSTALL"

Assumptions to the software
===========================

   @{b}NetCall@{ub} runs on Amigas equipped with AmigaOS 2.04 or later. AmigaOS
3.x  is, of course, supported, too.

   Additionally, you need @{i}TrapDoor@{ui} (1)   (not included in the
@{b}NetCall@{ub}-archive)  as a FidoNet-mailer. Other mailers may only be
used, if they use the same  shell-arguments and a compatible logfile
(@{b}NetCall@{ub} needs to scan the  @{i}TrapDoor@{ui}-logfile).

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  @{i}TrapDoor@{ui} is copyright  (C) Maximilian Hantsch and Martin Laubach


@EndNode

@Node "INSTALLER" "NetCall_English.guide/INSTALLER"
@Next "SHELL"
@Prev "SOFTWARE"
@Toc "INSTALL"

Installer
=========

   The installation is easily done by Commodore-Amiga's @{i}Installer@{ui}. Just
double-click on one of the install-icons (english or german language).
All  needed files will be copied to your hard-disk.

   After having installed @{b}NetCall@{ub}, you'll have to configure @{b}NetCall@{ub}  to
your wishes and to your FidoNet-software. Please read the
configuration-chapter  of this document for further information. See
also @{"Configuration" Link "CONFIG"}.

   Installer and Installer project icon  (c) Copyright 1991-93
Commodore-Amiga, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.   Reproduced and
distributed under license from Commodore.

   INSTALLER SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS-IS" AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE;  NO
WARRANTIES ARE MADE. ALL USE IS AT YOUR OWN RISK. NO LIABILITY  OR
RESPONSIBILITY IS ASSUMED.


@EndNode

@Node "SHELL" "NetCall_English.guide/SHELL"
@Next "WB"
@Prev "INSTALLER"
@Toc "INSTALL"

Execution from a shell
======================

   The following arguments may be passed if @{b}NetCall@{ub} is executed from a
shell:

      POLLID,CALL/K,CONFIG/K,OUTBOUND/K,PUBSCREENNAME/K,NOREQ/S,
      NOPOLL/S,NOCRASH/S,NOFREQ/S,ALLACTIVE/S,OPENBIG/S,TERMREQS/S,
      TELL/S

@{b}POLLID @{i}PollID(s)@{ui}@{ub}
     This is the @{i}ID@{ui} from your bosses, where you want @{b}NetCall@{ub} to poll.
     The  @{i}IDs@{ui} given here must correspond with the BOSS-entries in your
     @{b}NetCall.cfg@{ub}  (case-sensitive). You may pass a valid
     AmigaDOS-pattern as an argument here  (@{b}POLLID (BBS1|BBS2)@{ub} would
     cause @{b}NetCall@{ub} to poll at node @{i}BBS1@{ui} and  @{i}BBS2@{ui}).

@{b}CALL @{i}Node/Phone@{ui}@{ub}
     Node- or phone-number where you want @{b}NetCall@{ub} to poll

     (example: @{b}CALL 2:246/1045@{ub}).

@{b}CONFIG @{i}Config-file@{ui}@{ub}
     Use the given configuration-file rather than the normal
     configuration.

     (example: @{b}CONFIG Work:NetCall/Config2.cfg@{ub}).

@{b}OUTBOUND @{i}Outbound-path@{ui}@{ub}
     Scan this @{i}OUTBOUND@{ui}-directory rather than the directory specified
     in the  configurationfile.

@{b}PUBSCREENNAME @{i}public-screen@{ui}@{ub}
     Force to open @{b}NetCall@{ub}'s and the mailer's windows on this
     public-screen.

@{b}NOREQ@{ub}
     Use @{i}stdIO@{ui} for error-output rather than a system-requester.

@{b}NOPOLL@{ub}
     Do not pick up entries where @{b}NetCall@{ub} would just poll (in other
     words:  exclude your bosses).

@{b}NOCRASH@{ub}
     Exclude entries where @{b}NetCall@{ub} would crash mails to.

@{b}NOFREQ@{ub}
     Exclude entries where @{b}NetCall@{ub} would file-request from.

@{b}ALLACTIVE@{ub}
     Mark all entries as active immediately after @{b}NetCall@{ub} gets started.
     @{b}NetCall@{ub} will start to poll immediately.

@{b}OPENBIG@{ub}
     Always open @{b}NetCall@{ub}'s big window (two list-view-gadgets, one
     text-gadget).

@{b}TERMREQS@{ub}
     Forces @{b}NetCall@{ub} to terminate requesters (even error-requesters!)
     automatically. This option allows automatical operation without
     user-interaction.

@{b}TELL@{ub}
     If you are running @{i}TrapDoor@{ui} resident in the background, @{b}NetCall@{ub} may
     control @{i}TrapDoor@{ui} via the @{i}TrapTell@{ui}-command. To enable this option,
     specify @{i}TELL@{ui} as a shell-argument and define the @{i}TrapTell@{ui}-command
     in @{b}NetCall.cfg@{ub}. See also @{"Configuration of NetCall" Link "CONFIG"}.


@EndNode

@Node "WB" "NetCall_English.guide/WB"
@Prev "SHELL"
@Toc "INSTALL"

Execution from workbench
========================

   @{b}NetCall@{ub} can easily be started by double-clicking on it's icon.

   The following arguments may be passed as tool-types in the program
icon:

@{b}ARGS = <@{i}shell-args@{ui}>@{ub}
     All arguments, which can be passed as shell-arguments, can be
     passed in the  ARGS-tool-type, too. See also
     @{"Execution from a shell" Link "SHELL"}.

@{b}TOOLPRI = <@{i}priority (-127 to 128)@{ui}>@{ub}
     Taskpriority of @{b}NetCall@{ub}.


@EndNode

